```

Thanks a lot for this great piece of software - After the last version I unfortunately have a crash because the library doesn't use the provided context to override the allocations functions anymore.

~~~
tinybvh::BVH4_CPU blas;
blas.context = myContext;
blas.Build( vertices, triangleCount );
~~~

This internally will create more temporary Bvh structures which use the default memory context. Either the context needs to be copied, or maybe change the api to always pass the context into functions that require memory operations. 

I fixed it for my by setting the context member of both BVH structs on the way.

